HEADWORD: Tindal
<hw>Tin"dal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the native name:
cf. Malayalam <ets>ta<?/<?/al</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A petty
officer among lascars, or native East Indian sailors; a boatswain's
mate; a cockswain.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>
<rj><au>Malcom.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An attendant on an army.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tinder</ent>⟦br⟧
